{{Infobox zoo |zoo_name = Alexandria Aquarium |logo = |logo_caption = |image = Aquarium Museum, Alexandria (4592244000).jpg |image_caption = |location = [[Alexandria]], [[Egypt]] |date_opened = 1930 |date_closed = |coordinates = {{Coord|31.2128|29.8851|type:landmark_region:EG_scale:1000|display=it}} |area = |num_species = |num_animals = |largest_tank_vol = |total_tank_vol = |annual_visitors = |members = |exhibits = |website = }}
'''Alexandria Aquarium''' is a small [[public aquarium|aquarium]] in [[Alexandria]], [[Egypt]]. It was built in 1930 and is near [[Qaitbay fort]] on Alexandria's Eastern Harbour. The aquarium exhibits many species from the Mediterranean and Red Seas around Egypt, as well as some freshwater species from the Nile and the Amazon. Animals on display range from fish to crustaceans and turtles (both marine and freshwater). The Aquarium is also home to the Marine Research Institute..
[[Category:Aquaria in Egypt]] [[Category:Museums in Alexandria]] [[Category:Science museums in Egypt]] [[Category:Zoos established in 1930]]
