{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2017}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Larry King Now | image = Larrykingnow show card.jpg | caption = | genre = Talk show | starring = [[Larry King]] | country = United States | executive_producer = Jason Rovou | producer = | language = English | editor = | location = Los Angeles, California | cinematography = | camera = | runtime = | company = [[Ora TV]] | num_seasons = 4 | num_episodes = 549 | list_episodes = List of Larry King Now episodes | distributor = Ora TV, [[Hulu]], [[RT America]] | picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[16:9]] [[High-definition television|HDTV]]) | first_run = November 1, 2012 – present | first_aired = | preceded_by = ''[[Larry King Live]]'' }}
'''''Larry King Now''''' is a [[talk show]] hosted by [[Larry King]] created by Shawn Southwick King, and available on [[Ora TV]], [[Hulu]] and [[RT America]]. Launched on July 17, 2012, the series features interviews with newsmakers, celebrities, world leaders, and Internet stars. The show is similar to his previous [[CNN]] program, ''[[Larry King Live]]''.
The show is the first venture by Ora TV, an on-demand TV network founded in March 2012 by King, Shawn Southwick King, and [[Carlos Slim]].<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/sns-201207170101reedbusivarietynvr1118056646-20120717,0,312185.story|title = Larry King's 'Now' to stream on Hulu: Internet vid giant pacts with Carlos Slim Helu's Ora TV venture|first=Andrew |last=Wallenstein|work= [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]|date =July 17, 2012|accessdate=September 27, 2015}}</ref> In May 2013, [[RT America]] announced that ''Larry King Now'' would be broadcast on their network as well, along with the Ora TV show ''[[Politicking with Larry King]]''.<ref>{{cite web|first=Dylan|last=Byers|url=http://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2013/05/larry-king-joins-russian-channel-rt-164941.html|title=Larry King joins Russian channel RT|work=[[Politico]]|date=May 29, 2013|accessdate=September 27, 2015|publisher=[[Capitol News Company]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite press|url=http://rt.com/news/larry-king-joins-rt-873/|title=RT America to broadcast Larry King's new political show|work=[[RT (TV network)|RT News]]|date=May 29, 2013|accessdate=September 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Kenneth|last=Rapoza|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/kenrapoza/2013/06/06/larry-king-comes-out-of-retirement-joins-russian-tv/|title=Larry King Comes Out Of Retirement, Joins Russian TV|work=[[Forbes]]|publisher=Forbes, Inc.|date=June 6, 2013|accessdate=September 27, 2015}}</ref> Excerpts of both shows are also published on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/user/LarryKingNow |title=Larry King |author=Larry King |authorlink=Larry King |work=[[YouTube]] channel |year=2012 |accessdate=2018-03-20}}</ref>
