{{Infobox video game
| title = Spherical Worlds
| image= SphericalWorldsAmigaBoxFront.jpg
| developer = [[4-Matted]]
| publisher = [[Neo Software]]
| platforms = [[Amiga]]
| released = {{Video game release|EU|1996}}
| genre = [[Shoot 'em up]]
| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]]
| designer = Mirko Rizman
| programmer = Zvonko Tešić
| artist = {{Unbulleted list|Zvonko Tešić|Mirko Rizman}}
| writer = Mirko Rizman
| composer = {{Unbulleted list|Zvonko Tešić|Goran Štetić}}
}}

'''''Spherical Worlds''''' is a [[shoot 'em up]] [[video game]] developed by [[4-Matted]] and published by [[Neo Software]], released for [[Amiga]] platforms in 1996. The game plays from a [[top-down perspective]], from which the player the player controls a spherical [[battle droid]], shooting their way through an enemy battleship. The player can equip the droid with weapon and tool enhancements, such as additional weapons, [[power-up]]s, [[Extra life|extra lives]], and [[guided missile]]s, through a special weapon shop shown between game levels.

